    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangular container with two barriers parallel to the vertical sides of the container. The barriers separate the container into three sections labeled A, B, and C. The three sections are of equal size.\" src=\"/images/adb0c51ea78093b4b56134626fe1ae56.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A container with three sections initially contains samples of three different monatomic ideal gases, which are separated by removable barriers, as shown. The container is thermally isolated from its surroundings. The masses of gas atoms in gases <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span> are <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub A\"><math alttext=\"m sub A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub B\"><math alttext=\"m sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub C\"><math alttext=\"m sub C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>C</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, respectively, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub A is greater than m sub B, which is greater than m sub C\"><math alttext=\"m sub A is greater than m sub B, which is greater than m sub C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>C</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>. The initial temperatures gases <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span> are <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub A\"><math alttext=\"T sub A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub B\"><math alttext=\"T sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub C\"><math alttext=\"T sub C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mtext>C</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, respectively, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub C is greater than T sub B, which is greater than T sub A\"><math alttext=\"T sub C is greater than T sub B, which is greater than T sub A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mtext>C</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>. Both barriers are removed at the same time and the gases mix. Which of the following statements about the average kinetic energy of the gas atoms after the barriers are removed must be true?</p>\n",
